# Host platform output and domains

## Structured output

- CLI inventory/list commands: `@cmd(output=True)` + `emit_output(..., columns=...)`.
- MCP tools: `format_for_agent(..., format="text|md|json", columns=parse_columns(...))`.
- Do not duplicate `_json()` helpers — use cmdline.

## Domain ownership

- Ken domains live in `~/.config/ken/host/domains.yaml` (`owner: ken`).
- **Standard registrar for new Ken domains:** Cloudflare — migrate legacy at renewal (`host/docs/domains-and-dns.md`).
- Jeff/shared account domains: `owner: jeff` — inventory only unless user explicitly coordinates deploy.
- Never default `remote: ~/public_html` for addon domains — confirm docroot in cPanel first.

## Deploy safety

- `remote-prepare` is **manual first-time only** — never in CI.
- `host_deploy` / CI rsync: verify `host.yaml` `remote` matches cPanel document root before first deploy.
- Backup before any docroot mutation (`tar czf` or cPanel backup).

## Site spin-up target flow

Register (Cloudflare/Porkbun API) → DNS A record → cPanel addon → `sitehost mkweb` → CI on `main` → `host_inventory` confirms up.

See `host/docs/domains-and-dns.md`.
